== Other versions of the legendarium ==
In the twelfth note to a text written around [[1959]] and published in ''[[The Nature of Middle-earth]]'', it is said that either the slow maturity of the [[Half-elven]], or the "choice of kindred"<ref name="NOME"/>{{rp|78}} extended to the third generation, suggesting that Eldarion, and [[Tar-Amandil]], were among the Half-elven.<ref name="NOME"/>{{rp|82}} However, this was changed to the second generation in the actual text.<ref name="NOME"/>{{rp|78}} In the same text, Tolkien wrote that Eldarion had lived until the age of 125, most likely having passed away in [[Fourth Age|Fo.A. 126]].<ref name="NOME"/>{{rp|79}} However, it predates the second edition of ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'', where the date of Aragorn's death was ultimately changed by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] from {{FoA|100}} (as in the first edition) to {{FoA|120}}.<ref>{{PM|Shadow}}, Note 7</ref>{{rp|420}}

